Defendant in custody.   
Count 2 - Burglary - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1, 3, 4, and 5.   Motion granted.   Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of seven (7) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by five (5) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety except for current prescribed medications for mental health;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
6) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge;
7) Obtain HSED/GED;
8) Pay costs of action; 
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) Pay restitution as follows:   $136.26 to Walmart Stores Inc., P.O. Box 504765, St. Louis, MO 63150; $1,789.89 to Kohl's Department Store, 4411 Dewey Street, Manitowoc, WI  54220; $128.88 to Walmart Stores Inc., P.O. Box 504765, St. Louis, MO 63150; $251.96 to Shopko, 3415 Calumet Ave., Manitowoc, WI 54220; $1,308.54 to Jesse Springstube, 2404 Wilson St., Two Rivers, WI  54241.
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  
Defendant is given credit for 127 days time served.  
